{"type":"message","id":"8f1a590f","parentId":"fba286f1","timestamp":"2026-03-20T00:38:39.926Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No apps registered. So the X API isn't set up yet. I need to let Bobby know this. According to the skill:\n\n1. App credential registration must be done manually by the user outside the agent/LLM session\n2. The user must fill `~/.xurl` with required secrets manually on their own machine\n3. I should NOT try to pass secrets via the agent\n\nLet me explain this to Bobby.","thinkingSignature":"c7382a8770f60cd9509447e6597edfddc116b7bd0f441ce268f10efa19815223"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n\nHere's the thing though — the X API isn't set up yet. `xurl` shows no apps registered, which means nobody's authenticated to access your X account.\n\nTo get in there and look at your FYP, likes, bookmarks etc., you'll need to set up the API access first. Bobby, you gotta do this part yourself outside this chat:\n\n1. Go to https://developer.x.com\n2. Create a project + app (or use an existing one)\n3. Run `xurl auth apps add` to register it\n4. Then `xurl auth oauth2` to connect your account\n\nOnce that's done I can dive right in and scope out what you're into. \n\nYou said X API setup was pending in my notes — now I know why lmao. Want me to walk you through it or you got it? ⚡🕶️\n\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10285,"output":271,"cacheRead":12857,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23413,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773967108003}}
