{"type":"message","id":"64aa5fef","parentId":"bfe974ec","timestamp":"2026-03-20T01:14:01.785Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_89jq3t0tmg5u_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the image provided, here are the details of the visible tweets:\n\n### **Tweet 1 (Main Focus)**\n*   **Reposted by:** Kimberly Auer\n*   **Original Account Name:** Rip Cord 🇺🇸\n*   **Handle:** @TheRipCord\n*   **Time since posting:** 4h\n*   **Full Text:** \"Add on to the quoted post below in regards to 'Tippy Top'... Watch the Fox News clock right after Trump says 'Tippy Top' it turns over to 12:03 and hits the drop 991 timestamp exactly. 💥 h/t @HuxleySThompson\"\n*   **Political Topics/News/Opinions:** This tweet expresses support for **QAnon conspiracy theories**. It specifically references \"drop 991\" (referring to a post on an anonymous message board from April 2018) and claims a synchronous link between Donald Trump’s verbal use of the phrase \"Tippy Top\" and a time change on a Fox News broadcast. The opinion expressed is that these occurrences are coordinated signals or \"proofs\" of a clandestine plan.\n\n### **Tweet 2 (Quoted inside the first tweet's image)**\n*   **Account Name:** Keith Blumensaadt\n*   **Handle:** @BlumensaatKeith\n*   **Time since posting:** 4h\n*   **Full Text:** \"Replying to @truestormyjoe Tippy Top and Central casting in one Sentence ☔️🇺🇸🦅\"\n*   **Political Topics/News/Opinions:** This tweet highlights Donald Trump's use of signature phrases like \"Tippy Top\" and \"Central casting.\" The use of the umbrella, US flag, and eagle emojis suggests a **patriotic or pro-Trump sentiment**, likely within the same QAnon-adjacent context of looking for \"coded\" language in the former President’s speeches.\n\n### **Tweet 3 (Partially visible at the bottom)**\n*   **Account Name:** Rip Cord 🇺🇸\n*   **Handle:** @TheRipCord\n*   **Time since posting:** 8h\n*   **Full Text (Visible Part):** \"Trump saying 'Tippy Top' today while wearing a yellow tie. IYKYK... 🗂️ x.com/BlumensaatKeit...\"\n*   **Political Topics/News/Opinions:** Similar to the first tweet, this post focuses on Trump's rhetoric and appearance (the yellow tie) as potentially significant. The acronym **\"IYKYK\" (If You Know, You Know)** is a common shorthand in conspiracy communities to imply that there is a hidden, deeper meaning behind mundane details that only \"enlightened\" followers will understand. It reinforces the **pro-Trump, QAnon-themed** narrative of the account.\n\n---\n**Summary of Themes:** All visible tweets revolve around the **QAnon movement**, specifically focusing on \"decoding\" the actions and speech of **Donald Trump** to find proof of a grander conspiracy or plan. They utilize specific vocabulary (\"drops,\" \"Tippy Top\") and symbols common within that digital community."}],"details":{"model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/x_home3.png","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773969241775}}
