{"type":"message","id":"3e1954b1","parentId":"d205f0f5","timestamp":"2026-03-20T02:18:21.756Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's 10:18 PM on March 19. Tomorrow morning... let's say 9:00 AM or 10:00 AM. I'll set a cron job for 9:30 AM tomorrow. I need to use the cron tool to schedule a message that texts him.\n\nThe cron action should be \"add\" with a schedule and a payload that sends a message. Since it's a main session, I should use payload.kind=\"systemEvent\" with sessionTarget=\"main\". But wait - he wants me to \"shoot him a text\" which means send a Telegram message. Let me check... the cron job can deliver via the announce delivery with a channel and target.\n\nActually, for a reminder, I should use a system event and reply in the session. \n\nI need to figure out the right approach here - whether to use systemEvent to inject a reminder into the session, or agentTurn to actually send a message. Since he's on Telegram and wants a text, the cleanest solution is to set up an isolated agentTurn job that sends him a message directly using the message tool, rather than relying on systemEvent which might not reach him properly.","thinkingSignature":"d69a2da262044bb5d400513ea5d97f30d46337824b368d5f06388c037273a047"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aubxa7uxde7l_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"X account cleanup reminder","schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"30 9 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Text Bobby a reminder to clean out his X account posts and start fresh. He wanted to delete his old posts and start posting consistently. This is his X account: @bobbygalletta"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8212808444"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26784,"output":393,"cacheRead":19444,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46621,"cost":{"input":0,"outp