{"type":"message","id":"6fda8452","parentId":"71935ac8","timestamp":"2026-03-21T17:27:50.157Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to test the reminder system to make sure it works without any failures. Let me set a cron job and then immediately manually check if it would work, or set one up and see if it fires without errors.\n\nActually, the simplest way to test: just set a cron job for a couple minutes from now and see if it delivers successfully. If it works, great. If it fails, we'll see the error. But given the inconsistent behavior, it might fail.\n\nActually wait - I should just be honest. We've tested this multiple times and it's been inconsistent. The isolated agent for agent \"x\" has spotty Telegram connectivity. We've already established this. The only way to truly test would be to set a cron and wait, but we already know it fails sometimes.\n \nI could set a reminder for a few minutes out and watch what happens, but we've already seen this pattern fail multiple times - 1:07pm failed, 3:32pm worked, 5:30pm failed. Bobby's asking how to verify this won't happen again, but the reality is the isolated agent itself has connectivity issues that I can't really fix.\n\nThe most honest approach is to just pick a time a few minutes from now, set the cron, and let it run - if it fails, we'll see exactly what goes wrong. But honestly, given how unreliable this has been, maybe I should just send reminders manually instead of relying on cron jobs at all.","thinkingSignature":"ad33145e4e3605e8716f2368dadb97de67c38eb99bdcf622b7fa51ec0ad06e25"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me set one for a few minutes from now and we'll see what happens.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q71swi363fun_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"Test reminder","schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"32 13 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Text Bobby on Telegram: 'Test reminder. ⚡🕶️'"},