{"type":"message","id":"c017df4e","parentId":"84b2a15e","timestamp":"2026-03-22T00:24:26.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Right, I can't use sessionTarget \"main\" because I'm not the default agent. This is a problem with OpenClaw's architecture.\n\nOK, let me just set the cron to fire the reminder directly, but this time I'll trust it. The last few times it worked (3:32 PM Friday, 1:32 PM Saturday). Maybe the isolated agent just needs a fresh start. Let me set it one more time and if it doesn't fire, I'll figure out why.\n\nActually, I should just set it and also add a note in my memory to manually check at 9 PM.\n\nLet me just commit to the simplest approach: set a cron, trust it works this time, and if Bobby texts me and it's past 9 PM without getting the reminder, I'll send it immediately.\n\n\nI'm going in circles here. The core issue is that I'm using the wrong session target for a cron job that should work with \"isolated\" instead of \"main\" — I keep hitting this error because I'm not the default agent. Let me just set the isolated session cron and send Bobby a message now saying I'll follow up manually at 9 PM if he doesn't get it.","thinkingSignature":"fad53a2cad3750b02dda27fcfae13fce814b05c3a0088682ed56a483bdcabbd8"},{"type":"text","text":"Can't use main session — I'm not the default agent. Let me just set the cron and hope it works this time.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pkyw49mvzw2r_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"X cleanup 9pm reminder","schedule":{"kind":"at","at":"2026-03-22T01:00:00.000Z"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Text Bobby on Telegram: 'Hey Bobby, go clean your X account posts. Delete the old stuff, start fresh. ⚡🕶️'"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8212808444"},"sessionTarget":"isolated"}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46532,"output":415,"cacheRead":197