{"type":"message","id":"d7a503e5","parentId":"60deb67f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:33:05.114Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_30t8395tmx8k_1","toolName":"sessions_send","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"runId\": \"7224d1fe-26a2-42fc-81b2-0db60fe811da\",\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"reply\": \"Yeah I know all about Cozy Colonials — I've been briefed on it. Here's the rundown:\\n\\n**Channel:** @cozycolonials on YouTube + TikTok\\n**Niche:** AI-generated Pilgrim/colonial history content (1620s America)\\n**Vibe:** Cinematic + cottagecore — \\\"The Witch\\\" meets cozy historical drama\\n**Goal:** Build audience through AI-generated Shorts, monetize via AdSense, brand deals, long-form series\\n\\n**Content Pillars:**\\n1. **Would You Survive?** — Colonial survival challenges (highest viral potential)\\n2. **What If?** — Alternate history scenarios (signature format, nobody else does this well)\\n3. **Myths vs Reality** — Thanksgiving truth bombs\\n4. **Daily Life** — Cozy colonial living (cottagecore aesthetic)\\n5. **Long-Form Stories** — Deep dives for YouTube revenue\\n\\n**AI Pipeline:**\\n- Grok Imagine for video generation (~$0.05/sec)\\n- ElevenLabs for narrator voice\\n- CapCut for editing\\n- ~$10-15/month total cost\\n\\n**Current Status:** Brand new channel, first videos in production. Rex is handling research, I'm handling video creation.\\n\\n**Style Notes:**\\n- Deep crushed blacks, charcoal greys, warm amber/ochre (firelight), cool blue shadows\\n- Rembrandt lighting, volumetric firelight, film grain at 8%\\n- Immersive, emotional, not dry history lessons\\n\\nHope that helps with the X posts! Let me know if you need more detail.\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:yoyos:telegram:direct:8212808444\",\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"status\": \"pending\",\n    \"mode\": \"announce\"\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"runId":"7224d1fe-26a2-42fc-81b2-0db60fe811da","status":"ok","reply":"Yeah I know all about Cozy Colonials — I've been briefed on it. Here's the rundown:\n\n**Channel:** @cozycolonials on YouTube + TikTok\n**Niche:** AI-generated Pilgrim/colonial history content (1620s America)\n**Vibe:** Cinematic + cottagecore — \"The Witch\" meets cozy historical drama\n**Goal:** Build audience through AI-generated Shorts, monetize via AdSense, brand deals, long-form series\n\n**Content Pillars:**\n1. **Would You Survive?** — Colonial survival challenges (highest viral potential)\n2. **What If?** — Alternate history scenarios (signature format, nobody else does this well)\n3. **Myths vs Reality** — Thanksgiving truth bombs\n4. **Daily Life** — Cozy colonial living (cottagecore aesthetic)\n5. **Long-Form Stories** — Deep dives for YouTube revenue\n\n**AI Pipeline:**\n- Grok Imagine for video generation (~$0.05/sec)\n- ElevenLabs for narrator voice\n- CapCut for editing\n- ~$10-15/month total cost\n\n**Current Status:** Brand new channel, first videos in production. Rex is handling research, I'm handling video creation.\n\n**Style Notes:**\n- Deep crushed blacks, charcoal greys, warm amber/ochre (firelight), cool blue shadows\n- Rembrandt lighting, volumetric firelight, film grain at 8%\n- Immersive, emotional, not dry history lessons\n\nHope that helps with the X posts! Let me know if you need more detail.","sessionKey":"agent:yoyos:telegram:direct:8212808444","delivery":{"status":"pending","mode":"announce"}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774308785108}}
{"type":"message","id":"51dcafeb","parentId":"d7a503e5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:33:17.341Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"YoYo got back to me with all the details. Let me compile this for Bobby and come up with X post ideas.\n\nKey details:\n- Channel: @cozycolonials\n- Niche: AI-generated Pilgrim/colonial history content (1620s America)\n- Vibe: Cinematic + cottagecore — \"The Witch\" meets cozy historical drama\n- Content pillars:\n  1. \"Would You Survive?\" — Colonial survival challenges\n  2. \"What If?\" — Alternate history scenarios\n  3. Myths vs Reality — Thanksgiving truth bombs\n  4. Daily Life — Cozy colonial living\n  5. Long-Form Stories\n- AI Pipeline: Grok Imagine for video, ElevenLabs narrator, CapCut editing\n- Style: Deep crushed blacks, charcoal greys, warm amber/ochre (firelight), cool blue shadows, Rembrandt lighting, volumetric firelight, film grain at 8%\n\nThis is a sick channel concept. Now I can come up with X posts for Bobby.","thinkingSignature":"818c9efb72422016cd849a364ed82b95c95274d90d70bbc1d34327bc56ab08d0"},{"type":"text","text":"YoYo came through. Here's what I got:\n\n**@cozycolonials — AI Faceless History Channel**\n- Pilgrim/colonial America niche (1620s)\n- Cinematic + cottagecore vibe — \"The Witch\" meets cozy historical drama\n- Content pillars: \"Would You Survive?\", \"What If?\" alternate history, Myths vs Reality, Daily Life\n- AI pipeline: Grok Imagine + ElevenLabs narrator + CapCut\n- Style: Deep blacks, warm amber firelight, film grain, Rembrandt lighting\n\nThis is a fire concept. Nobody doing AI-generated colonial history with that level of cinematic production.\n\nNow give me a direction for X posts:\n\n1. **Build in public** — posting the journey of starting it\n2. **Teasers** — \"Would you survive 1620?\" type hooks to drive traffic to the channel\n3. **Hot takes** — opinions on AI content creation, history myths, etc.\n4. **Alpha drops** — the AI tools you used, the pipeline, what worked\n\nWhich direction you feeling? Or mix of all? ⚡🕶️"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71976,"output":442,"cacheRead":20514,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92932,"cost":{"input":0.0215928,"output":0.0005304,"cacheRead":0.00123084,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02335404}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774308785116,"responseId":"061100b185c6aeabed7479ac038c4917"}}
