{"type":"message","id":"e68838ca","parentId":"083ef145","timestamp":"2026-03-29T06:33:29.012Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_six0k87cpxeb_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In the provided image, there are three main posts visible in the X (formerly Twitter) feed. Here is a detailed list:\n\n### 1. Elon Musk's Post\n*   **Account Name:** Elon Musk (verified with a blue checkmark)\n*   **Handle:** @elonmusk\n*   **Full Text:** \"Tesla FSD\"\n*   **Content:** This is an original post by Elon Musk that serves as a quote-repost of Peter H. Diamandis.\n*   **Quoted Content (by Peter H. Diamandis, MD):**\n    *   **Handle:** @PeterDiamandis\n    *   **Text:** \"Tesla's FSD: 5.3 million miles between accidents. US driving average: 660,000. That's 9x safer. And it's only getting better.\"\n*   **Topic:** Automotive technology, specifically Tesla's Full Self-Driving (FSD) software and its safety statistics compared to human drivers.\n\n### 2. DITOGAMES Advertisement\n*   **Account Name:** DITOGAMES (verified with a gold checkmark)\n*   **Handle:** @DITOGAMESch\n*   **Full Text:** \"If you have a mouse, you have to play this game.\"\n*   **Content:** This is a promoted post (Ad). It includes a high-definition video frame showing a military helicopter flying over a coastal/tropical environment. An overlay on the video says \"0:01 Play for free. No Installation.\" with a link to \"navy.quest\".\n*   **Topic:** Video gaming, specifically an advertisement for a free-to-play browser-based military game.\n\n### 3. Elon Musk Repost of Rothmus\n*   **Account Name:** Rothmus (followed by Elon Musk's repost indicator)\n*   **Handle:** @Rothmus\n*   **Full Text:** The specific text of this post is not fully visible, but it appears to be a repost from Elon Musk showing a profile picture of a person with a skull-like mask or face paint.\n*   **Topic:** Social commentary or humor (based on the typical content of the Rothmus account).\n\n---